    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-01T19:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-01T19:36:00-05:00" n="947"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d947">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.112 R 56/11.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-01T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Nine American citizens, including G. P. Robinson, wife and son, and one British
                    subject, fled before threatened assaults at the <pb facs="0847" n="731"
                        xml:id="pg_731"/> Suriana mine in the State of Guerrero, took refuge in
                    Telolcapan and urgently requested aid. I made urgent personal representations to
                    the Department of Gobernacion, which sent instructions to General Vego to
                    furnish an escort. British Minister has made similar representations. I will
                    also make usual representations to Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
